title: Is this homemade MATCHA BOBA actually worth the effort?
description:
Is this homemade MATCHA BOBA actually worth the effort?

‚ú®Recipe: 
‚ú®Prepare the brown sugar boba pearls: In a small saucepan, combine the 1/3cup water and 1/3cup light brown sugar. Heat mixture over high heat until boiling. Reduce the heat to low and mix in 1/2cup of tapioca starch, stirring constantly for 6-8 seconds. Remove from heat and mix in another 1/2cup of tapioca starch until a dough just begins to form. 
Dump the dough out onto a work surface and knead until a smooth dough forms, about 1 minute or so. Working quickly, as the dough will dry up if it cools too much, divide the dough into four equal pieces and roll each piece into a long rod and then cut and form into little balls. 
‚ú®Place the boba pearls into a bowl with tapioca starch and toss to coat. Dump the boba into a fine-mesh sieve to shake off the excess tapioca starch. 
‚ú®To cook the boba pearls, heat a medium pot of water over medium-high heat until boiling. Add the pearls and boil for 30 minutes. Cut the heat and let the pearls rest in the water for 20-25 minutes or until translucent and chewy. 
‚ú®Make the Brown Sugar Syrup:  To a small saucepot, add 6 1/2 TBLS of water and 1 1/4cup light brown sugar and swirl to combine. Place over medium heat and cook until the sugar dissolves and the mixture starts to bubble. Increase the heat to medium-high and boil vigorously to reduce the liquid into a syrup. Drain the pearls through a fine-mesh strainer. Stir into the syrup mixture along with 1 tbls of blackstrap molasses. 
‚ú®To assemble with traditional milk tea, add 2cups of whole milk to a small saucepan over medium heat. Heat the milk until it reaches 162¬∞F (72¬∞C), stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and mix in 5 black tea bags. Let steep for 4-8 minutes, or until it reaches the desired strength of flavor. Refrigerate until completely cold. To a tall glass, spoon in as many boba pearls as desired and top with desired amount of syrup. Add in the ice cubes before pouring in the chilled milk tea and serve. 
‚ú®To assemble the matcha, I used a specific boba matcha powder. Heat 2 cups milk like above, and pour in the matcha according to package. Assemble the same way as above. Enjoy! üòâ

i used to struggle to make my matcha lattes taste good, but after lots of trial and error, i finally figured out how to make my perfect latte! hopefully this helps you if you‚Äôre struggling too üíö

what other tips do you have that i missed?

matcha mistakes you might be making:
1. using a low quality matcha
2. using too little matcha
3. using too much water
4. using boiling water
5. using overpowering milk
6. using too much milk

p.s. for the milk ratio, i usually just add an additional 10ml of milk for every additional gram of matcha I use! So 3g matcha/80ml milk, 4g matcha/90ml milk, 5g matcha/100ml milk, 6g matcha/110ml milk, etc. This helps keep the matcha flavor strong! üíö

description:
The answer, if you ask me, is any plant milk you like BUT I would not recommend dairy milk, and I promise I‚Äôm not just saying that because I‚Äôm vegan.

When you mix matcha directly with milk, the casein protein in dairy milk binds to polyphenols in matcha, alters the bioavailability and blocks absorption of antioxidants. In short, you‚Äôre missing out on potential health benefits that matcha has to offer.

The good news is, this isn‚Äôt an issue with plant milk, so opt for something like oat, almond, soy or whatever else you‚Äôd like! It‚Äôs better for the planet anyway üôÇ

How to make matcha tea properly!
description:
This is how to prepare matcha correctly at home!

1. Sift 1-2 teaspoons of matcha to remove clumps.
2. Heat water to just below boiling.
3. Soak your bamboo whisk in warm water.
4. Mix a bit of hot water with the matcha.
5. Whisk vigorously in a "W" pattern until frothy.
6. Add more water for a thinner drink, if desired.
7. Sip immediately to enjoy it at its best.
Perfecting matcha takes practice, but it's well worth the effort!

description:
To make the perfect cup of matcha tea, you need to have the right tea brewing supplies. Gather your matcha bowl, matcha powder, match bamboo whisk (Chasen), and matcha spoon (Chashaku). Both the bowl and spoon are necessary items to ensure you brew perfect cups of matcha tea. You will also need tea cups and a tea pot to boil the water used to prepare the matcha. 

Brewing Matcha Tips:
‚Ä¢ Always soak the Chasen in warm water before whisking.
‚Ä¢ Sift the matcha green tea powder through a sieve to remove any lumps.
‚Ä¢ Never pour the boiling water directly into the matcha bowl. 

Traditional Japanese tea ceremonies utilize a matcha tea set that includes everything you need to brew matcha. You can find match tea sets, as well as high-quality powdered match green tea at Den‚Äôs Tea or call us directly at 877-DENS-TEA (877-336-7832) for further information or assistance. 

For high-quality, authentic Japanese matcha green tea, please browse our selection:

title: Matcha Tiramisu | Dzung Duong
description:
Dzung Duong, aka Honeysuckle, makes her debut with 'Matchamisu', which is Tiramisu made with Japanese green tea matcha powder. Delicate, fluffy and delightful! 

Subscribe to Dzung's channel: http://taste.md/1YlriBF

INGREDIENTS 

For the matcha cream:

6 egg yolks
3/4 cup white sugar
1/2 cup milk
16 oz  or 2 ¬Ω cups mascarpone cheese
1 1/4 cups cold heavy cream
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 tbsp matcha powder
An additional ¬Ω cup of matcha powder for dusting.

For the matcha cake:

2 packets of lady fingers (ones from Trader Joe‚Äôs is good)
1 cup boiling water
1/2 cup sugar
1 tbsp matcha powder

RECIPE 

In a medium sauce, heat milk until steaming. 

In a separate bowl, whisk egg yolks with sugar and matcha powder. When the milk begins to steam, slowly temper the egg yolks by adding ¬º cup of milk and whisk vigorously. Add the rest of the milk and whisk until combined.

Next, mix in mascarpone cheese and set aside.

Using a stand or hand mixer, whip heavy cream with vanilla extract. Continue to beat until it reaches stiff peaks. Gently fold in mascarpone matcha mixture, a little bit at a time. Set aside.

Now, for the matcha cake:

In a bowl, combine boiling water, ¬º cup sugar and 1 tbsp matcha. Stir until dissolved. Taking one lady finger at a time, dip into Matcha mixture. 

Continue to dip lady fingers and line in a row at bottom of glass baking dish. 

Add a thin layer of the mascarpone matcha cream on top and dust with more matcha powder. Continue to layer until it reaches the top of baking dish. Dust with more matcha powder to cover.

Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

A Green Tea Latte needs no introduction. This drink has been quite popular over the past few years with it's complex flavor - slightly bitter and chock full of healthy antioxidants that help prevent cancer. One of my resolutions is to keep a healthy lifestyle this year. I think this green tea latte will help! 

Green Tea Latte Recipe:

Ingredients:
- 1 cup of soy milk 
- 1 tsp of sugar and 
- 1 tsp of vanilla extract.
- 2 tsp of green tea powder 
- 1 tbsp of hot water. 

Preparation:

I'm starting by heating up 1 cup of soy milk with 1 tsp of sugar and 1 tsp of vanilla extract. I love using soy milk because its natural flavors pair really well with the matcha green tea powder, but you can use regular milk too. I'll heat it up on the stove just until the milk starts to steam. In the meantime I'll prep my green tea. 

I bought my powder at the local Japanese market, but you can find this at Teavana at the mall too.I'm using 2 tsp of green tea powder but you can use less if the green tea flavor is too intense for you. I'm just going to add the powder to my mug and mix it with 1 tbsp of hot water. This will help to dissolve the powder and prevent it from clumping up later when I add my milk. 

Now, I'll add in my steamed milk to the mug, let it combine and enjoy! Cheers to our health this year! I'd love to know what you're going to improve on. Let me know by commenting below and I'll catch you on the next Coffee Break! Bye

title: how to create the smoothest matcha microfoam in 1 minute üçµüíö

matcha i'm using: https://mizubatea.com/?rfsn=8679532.232417

üå∏ my sakura chasen charm is from @BijouxKomorebi! (my small jewelry business) ü©∑ shop here: https://bijouxkomorebi.com/products/sakura-chasen-charm

üí° STEPS: 
1Ô∏è‚É£ use a high quality matcha powder (i used Mizuba Tea Co‚Äôs Daily matcha - https://bit.ly/42IwLbP). does not need to be ‚Äúceremonial‚Äù grade. however, ‚Äúculinary‚Äù grade might not produce your desired results. you may just need to use trial and error with what you have!

2Ô∏è‚É£ sift 3g matcha with 30ml of water at 170¬∞F / 77¬∞C. i like to use a 1:10 ratio of matcha to water. also, sifting helps remove clumps and produces a smoother end result

3Ô∏è‚É£ whisk vigorously yet gently in a W back-and-forth motion for 30 seconds until large bubbles form

4Ô∏è‚É£ slow down your speed and whisk just the surface to break up the large bubbles. do this for another 30 seconds or so. you may need to whisk longer and/or slower to break up the bubbles

that‚Äôs it! your foam should look glassy and smooth. enjoy it as is or over a cup of milk ü•õ

Ube Cream Matcha Latte: A Bold Fusion with My New Matcha Ceremonia Kit
There‚Äôs nothing quite like the moment when you find your new favorite drink‚Äîespecially when it‚Äôs a colorful, delicious, and unique blend of flavors. Lately, I‚Äôve been obsessed with the Ube Cream Matcha Latte, a drink that combines the smooth earthiness of matcha with the rich, creamy taste of ube. What makes it even more special is creating it using my new matcha essential kit, which elevates the experience to a whole new level!

Today, I‚Äôm sharing the recipe for this dreamy Ube Cream Matcha Latte, and trust me, once you try it, you‚Äôll be hooked too.

What You'll Need:
Matcha (~2 tsps)
Milk (100ml)
Heavy Cream (50ml)
Ube Extract (1 tbsp, add sugar if you want it sweeter)
Ladyfinger (for garnish)
How to Make Ube Cream Matcha Latte
Step 1: Cold Whisked Matcha
The base of this latte starts with a beautifully whisked matcha. I use 2 teaspoons of matcha and whisk it with 100ml of cold milk using the tools from my matcha ceremonia kit. The bamboo whisk creates a perfectly smooth and frothy matcha blend that is absolutely essential for achieving the right texture and flavor.

Pro Tip: Whisk in a ‚ÄúW‚Äù motion to create an even froth. This technique, combined with the traditional whisk from the kit, ensures your matcha is well-blended and free of clumps.

Step 2: Ube Cream
Next comes the star of the drink‚Äîube cream. In a small bowl, whip 50ml of heavy cream with 1 tablespoon of ube extract. You can adjust the sweetness by adding sugar to taste, but I personally love the subtle sweetness of ube on its own. The result is a thick, luscious purple cream that‚Äôs full of rich flavor.

Step 3: Layering the Drink
Pour the cold whisked matcha into a glass, and then gently spoon the ube cream on top. The visual contrast between the deep green matcha and the vibrant purple ube cream is stunning‚Äîit‚Äôs a feast for the eyes as much as it is for the taste buds!

Step 4: Topping It Off
For an extra treat, I like to top my Ube Cream Matcha Latte with a ladyfinger. It adds a delightful crunch and makes the experience of drinking this latte feel even more indulgent.

Why the Matcha Ceremonia Kit is a Must-Have
Ever since I got my matcha essential kit, making matcha has become more than just preparing a drink‚Äîit‚Äôs a mindful ritual that I look forward to every day. The bamboo whisk is perfect for creating the right consistency, and the whole kit brings an authentic and calming vibe to the process. Using the traditional tools helps me connect with the rich history of matcha preparation while also making it easier to achieve that perfect froth.

Final Thoughts
The Ube Cream Matcha Latte is not just a treat for the taste buds‚Äîit‚Äôs a drink that‚Äôs as visually striking as it is flavorful. The earthy notes of matcha blend perfectly with the creamy, nutty flavor of ube, and when you add in the elegance of the ceremonia kit, making this latte feels like a creative, satisfying process.

If you‚Äôre looking for something new to try, give this recipe a go! And don‚Äôt forget, a matcha essential kit can make all the difference in creating the perfect drink, helping you bring both tradition and taste into every cup.

title: Mochi Ice Cream was invented in America??
description:
Recipe‚§µÔ∏è Would you eat this?

Matcha Mochi Ice Cream

Ingredients:
1 cup glutinous rice flour, plus more for dusting
¬º cup granulated sugar
2 tsp matcha powder
‚Öî cup water
Green tea ice cream, for filling

Directions:
In a bowl, combine the rice flour, sugar, and matcha powder
Add in the water, then whisk until smooth
In a nonstick pan on medium/ low heat, cook the rice flour mixture until thickened, stirring constantly with a nonstick spatula
The mixture will become a dough, once that happens, fold it over itself a few times, then remove from the heat
Dust a glass bowl with a bit of rice flour, then add the mochi dough into it
Pound with a wooden pestle, folding it over itself occasionally, until you heat a popping sound
Dust a flat surface with rice flour and roll the dough out into a log around 1 ¬Ω inch
Divide into 8 pieces
Roll each piece into a ball, then flatten it
Place over a small bowl, letting the edges dangle over the sides
Place a small scoop of the green tea ice cream in the center, then bring the sides of the dough over it to completely close
Cut off any excess dough and add a bit of rice flour on top to make it less sticky
Place in the freezer so that the ice cream doesn‚Äôt melt while you repeat for the rest of the dough
Once ready to serve, dust with more matcha powder

Enjoy!!

title: Mango Matcha ü•≠
description:
My dream is to open an Asian caf√©, and I‚Äôm building a menu one drink at a time with you here! This Mango Matcha recipe is sweet, earthy, and absolutely perfect for summer. 

1 ripe mango 
2 tbsps honey 
1.5 tsps matcha powder 
2 Tbsps hot water 
1/2 cup milk of choice 
Lots of ice 

Process: 

- Chop the mango super fine, add honey and continue chopping 
- Pass the matcha powder through a sieve and whisk with a matcha bamboo whisk that has been soaked in water 
- Whisk until nice and frothy 
- To assemble, start with the mango at the base, Top up with ice, pour over the milk and the matcha 
- Stir and enjoy chilled!

Matcha Fluffy yogurt recipe @katlieu (no pudding mix, no baking powder needed) (this is not guacamole Ingredients: 1 cup Greek Yogurt 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup, adjust to taste 1 tablespoon creamy or crunchy peanut butter Optionally, marshmallow root powder (see packaging for serving size, usually 2 small scoops with the scoop that comes in the bag) and 1 teaspoon collagen powder 1 teaspoon matcha powder (or swap out with cocoa powder, or extracts of your choice) Toppings: Fruits and berries of your choice 1 teaspoon hemp seeds (optional) Nuts of your choice Any of your favorite toppings go!! There‚Äôs at least 20 g of protein per serving. I split this in half with my mother. Instructions: 1. Mix the yogurt, honey or maple syrup, peanut butter, marshmallow root powder-- if using, and matcha together in a serving bowl until combined and fluffy, a minute. Top with your toppings of choice and enjoy!

title: Morning Matcha
description:
Here's the recipe: 

THE MORNING MATCHA 
(Created by IG: @Sacha_Tanha) 
2 oz. (60ml) Vodka 
2 oz. (60ml) Cinnamon infused Vanilla Almond Milk 
1 oz. (30ml) Honey Syrup
1 bar spoon Matcha Powder
Garnish: Cinnamon/Cane Sugar/ Matcha Powder

PREPARATION
1. In a shaking glass with ice, combine vodka, cinnamon infused vanilla almond milk, honey syrup, and matcha powder. Shake well. 
2. Strain mix into a glass and swift cinnamon, cane sugar, and matcha powder over. Enjoy responsibly!

title: Matcha milk jellyüçµüíö you asked so here‚Äôs the recipe! #matcha #jelly #dessertideas #easyrecipe
description:
Matcha milk jellyüçµüíö

Recipe:
1. Bloom 1.25 tsp of gelatin powder in 1 tbsp of cold water
2. Whisk 2 tsp matcha powder with a little bit of hot water to make a paste
3. Heat 1 cup milk and add in 1 tbsp sugar 
4. Add gelatin to hot milk and mix until fully dissolved
5. Mix in matcha paste and pour into container
6. Let set for at least 4 hours
7. Cut into rectangular shapes and enjoy!

title: Matcha Coconut Bars ‚ú®üçµ
description:
We came together to create these wholesome Matcha Coconut Bars ‚ú®üçµ Packed with the goodness of oats, almonds, coconut, and vibrant matcha from @breematcha, they‚Äôre the perfect feel-good snack! 

Ingredients: 
Almond butter - ¬Ω cup 
Maple syrup or honey - 5 tbsp 
Vanilla extract - 1 tsp 
Oats - toasted and pulsed - 1 cup 
Almonds - toasted and pulsed  - ¬Ω cup 
Desiccated coconut - ¬º cup 
Pumpkin seeds - ¬º cup 
Matcha powder - 1 tbsp 
Salt - pinch 

Matcha for dusting 

Method:
* Toast the oats and almonds in a pan until lightly golden and aromatic.
* Allow them to cool, then pulse into a coarse mix with small chunks‚Äînot a fine powder.
* In a mixing bowl, add the pulsed oats and almonds, almond butter, maple syrup (or honey), vanilla extract, desiccated coconut, pumpkin seeds, and salt. Mix well using a spatula or your hands.
* Add the matcha powder and mix until everything is evenly combined.
* Line a loaf tin with greased parchment paper and press the mixture evenly into the tin.
* Refrigerate the mixture for 10‚Äì12 minutes or until firm and set.
* Remove from the tin, cut into bars or squares as desired, and dust lightly with matcha powder before serving.

title: How to make Matcha | Usucha
description:
Usucha (or 'thin tea'), known for its vibrant green colour and creamy texture, is the most common way to drink matcha. While it may look sophisticated, its actually very easy to make!

Step 1: Heat your water.

Step 2: Preheat your bowl and whisk by pouring hot water into your bowl and let the whisk's prongs soak to soften them.

Step 3: Empty the bowl and wipe it dry.

Step 4: Sift 2 grams of matcha into your bowl.

Step 5: Add about 70ml (2.4oz) of 80¬∞C (176¬∞F) water.

Step 6: Whisk Away! Use a back and forth motion, keeping the whisk low in the bowl at first, then slowly raising it as foam starts to form. 

Step 7: Enjoy your usucha!

Read our guide to making usucha: https://www.tezumi.com/blogs/tezumi-insights/how-to-make-matcha-usucha

title: Matcha = Krankenhaus!? üçµüöë
description:
Nie wieder Matcha trinken!? üò¶ Denn mehrere Creator:innen sind angeblich wegen zu viel Matcha im Krankenhaus gelandet! Was ist da passiert?? Wir checken das f√ºr euch! üòº


Der erste Hinweis ist der Hashtag #Anemie unter den Videos ‚Äì also Blutarmut. Die kann verschiedene Ursachen haben, eine der h√§ufigsten ist Eisenmangel! Vor allem Frauen sind davon betroffen, weil sie zum Beispiel durch ihre Menstruationsblutung Eisen verlieren. üëÄ Aber was hat Matcha damit zu tun? ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è 


Die Oxals√§ure und Gerbstoffe im Matcha binden das Eisen an sich. Und das hei√üt: Es kann nicht vom K√∂rper ins Blut aufgenommen werden. ‚ùå Wir fragen zwei der Creator:innen an und sie erkl√§ren, dass sie Vorerkrankungen und daher Eisenmangel haben! Der Matcha sei also eine zus√§tzliche Belastung gewesen. ü§ïüçµ


Und die Ern√§hrungsexpertin Theresia Weimar-Ehl von der Verbraucherzentrale best√§tigt uns: Matcha allein blockiert nicht so viel Eisen, dass es zur Blutarmut kommt! üßë‚Äç‚öïÔ∏è Wenn ihr aber einen Eisenmangel habt, solltet ihr NICHT ohne Absprache Eisensupplements nehmen. Was da auf jeden Fall hilft: Vitamin C! Also zum Essen einfach eine Paprika oder ein Glas O-Saft snacken. üçäüòå

title: chai matcha bubble tea | fun and flavorful bubble tea recipes!
description:
Chai Matcha Bubble Tea üßã | Experience a fusion of flavors with our Masala Chai Matcha blend to make your Bubble Tea Day extra special! It's a little bit spicy, with some creamy and umami, and a whole lot of boba bubbly üòã

Ingredients
- 1 tsp Masala Chai Matcha powder
- 1/2 tsp Matcha.com matcha
- 1/4 cup hot water
- 2/3 cup milk
- 1/2 cup tapioca pearls
- 2 cups water
- 1/2 cup brown sugar
- ice

Instruction
‚Äî Boil 2 cups of water in a sauce pan, and add the tapioca pearls. Cook for 30 minutes on high heat, and strain in running water to remove the excess starch.
‚Äî Melt brown sugar in a clean sauce pan, and add in the tapioca pearls. Cook for 2 more minutes, then remove from the heat. Let cool.
‚Äî Sift chai matcha powder in a chawan. Add hot water, and whisk until frothy.
‚Äî In a glass, add the brown sugar tapioca pearls, ice, milk, and the chai matcha. Enjoy!

title: Matcha pancakes with mango yogurt sauce ü§§ü•≠üçµ #caregiver
description:
Here‚Äôs an easy breakfast that the whole family loves! 

My partner is 84-year-old mom requires soft and lower sodium food. Typically she starts her day off with a big bowl of steel cut oats. But on the weekends, we like to mix things up a bit and indulge a little bit more 

So here‚Äôs how I make a super simple breakfast by combining boxed pancake mix with Matcha. So simple to make, feels gourmet, and it‚Äôs absolutely delicious.

To add a bit more nutrients to the mix, I topped it off with a Greek yogurt sauce. But of course, I had to be a little bit extra about it, and added some mango jam to it. 

I topped it off with lots of strawberries. 

And to make sure we had some protein for our breakfast, I scrambled up eggs. 

If you need to feed the kids, adult adults, and an aging parent, you might want to give this one to try.

title: Grinding my own matcha in Japan at this fully booked workshop!
description:
Matcha Grinding Details üëá

Looking for a unique hands-on experience in Japan? Try grinding your own matcha in Uji, the heart of Japan‚Äôs matcha culture.

üìç Fukujuen Uji Tea Factory (Á¶èÂØøÂúíÂÆáÊ≤ªÂ∑•Êàø)

This popular spot lets you grind matcha with a traditional stone mill and experience how real matcha is made from start to finish.

Reservations fill up several weeks in advance, so plan ahead if you can!

üçµ ABOUT THE MATCHA GRINDING EXPERIENCE üçµ

You‚Äôll learn the full matcha-making process from the instructors: from hand-picked leaves to fine matcha powder.

Each session takes about an hour and ends with a mini tea ceremony and optional seasonal sweets, where you can enjoy the matcha you made yourself.

We‚Äôve joined other matcha workshops in Uji before, but this one stood out for the size of the facility and how in-depth the experience is. 

Some other workshops only let you grind for a few minutes, so this one feels much more immersive.

With that said, if you can‚Äôt get a reservation or don‚Äôt want to spend too much time, smaller tea shops around Uji offer quick matcha grinding experiences that are great for last-minute trips.

title: Trying Maruwu Seicha‚Äôs Peach Matcha Latte üçëüçµ #matcha #matchalatte #bayarea
Making a Mango Sticky Rice Matcha Latte ü•≠üçµ #mango #matcha #matchalatte
description:
Making a matcha latte üçµ‚Ä¶but mango sticky rice flavored! Mango sticky rice ü•≠ is easily one of my favorite desserts and the combination of ripe mangoes and coconut cream pairs so well with matcha. Soo be sure to save this post if you need some summertime ‚òÄÔ∏è matcha inspiration! 

Ingredients
¬Ω mango (pureed) + agave (depending on preferred sweetness)

4g matcha powder (from @matchakari)
40ml hot water (preferably at 175F)
120ml milk of choice

2 tbsp of heavy cream
1 tbsp of coconut cream
1 tsp condensed milk
Pinch of salt

Sprinkle of black sesame seeds
Sprig of mint
Drizzle of condensed milk

Recipe
Puree half a mango in a food processor or blender. Add agave if mango is not sweet. Optional: save a few pieces of mango for garnish.
For the cream topping, blend together heavy cream, coconut cream, and pinch of salt. Set aside.
Prepare matcha by sifting matcha powder and whisking with hot water.
Layer in order: mango puree, ice, milk, matcha, cream.
Top with cubed mangoes, a drizzle of condensed milk, sprig of mint, and black sesame seeds
Mix and enjoy!

üí° Inspired by @loveemanda and @ispillice to make this unique drink!

title: Strawberry cream cold foam matcha latte | better than Starbucks and easy to make!#strawberrymatcha
Matcha ve Ye≈üil √áay Aslƒ±nda Aynƒ± Bitki Desem :) #matcha #ye≈üil√ßay #saƒülƒ±k #icecek #tarif
WHY I QUIT COFFEE // MY HONEY MATCHA LATTE
description:
I had no idea my 1-month experiment swapping coffee for matcha would make me such a die hard matcha fan üòÜ When I started bringing awareness to my hormone health last year I took a long, hard look at what habits of mine weren't supporting healthy hormones and my morning double espresso latte started to set off alarm bells üö®

I realized that coffee made me experience jitters and anxiety that manifested both physically (restlessness, sweating, shakiness) and mentally (irritability, trouble concentrating). I had to come to terms with the reality that the relationship I had with my morning coffee was toxic - I loved it but it didn't love me back ü•≤ So I made the switch and this is what I experienced: 

- Weeks 1 and 2 I CRAVED coffee. Matcha just didn't hit the same or give me that BURST of "let's goooo" energy that I had become dependent on to will myself into conquering the day
- Week 3 I started to adapt to the change and didn't think about coffee. I also got used to the slow-release caffeine in matcha that provides a more gradual increase in energy 
- Week 4 I had a coffee while traveling and it tasted BAD. I did not enjoy it at all, and not in a "this is bad coffee" way but in a "my tastebuds have reset and I don't like this" way 
- After that there was no looking back! My coffee cravings were gone, I'd fully come to appreciate the taste, ritual, and feeling of matcha, and I no longer even liked coffee. 

I actually had a coffee a month ago when the coffee shop we frequent was out of matcha and all those old symptoms of shakiness, trouble focusing, and anxiety rushed back üòµ‚Äçüí´ thus proving to me why I made the switch!

HONEY MATCHA LATTE‚ú® 
1 tsp matcha powder (I used @piquelife - discount in my bio)
3 oz cold water 
1/2 - 1 tsp honey (I like @manukora manuka honey)
1/3 cup creamy vanilla cashew milk (recipe in my January reels)

To make your latte:
Add the water to a small glass or bowl 
Spoon the matcha powder through a fish mesh sieve to break up any clumps 
Whisk in a front to back motion until slightly frothy on top 
Add the honey and whisk again 
Add ice to your serving glass 
Pour in the milk and top with your honey matcha mixture 
ENJOY!

title: Iced Mango Matcha Latte Tutorial üçµü•≠
description:
Iced mango matcha latteüëáüèºüçµ Obsessed with this flavour combo! May even be better than strawberry matcha ü§≠

Give it a try and follow for more @tessbegg

I use Kenko Tea Organic Ceremonial Matcha Powder. The quality, colour & taste is always amazing! Get 15% off with my code TESSBEGG ü´∂üèº (affiliate) go to: bit.ly/tess-matcha

Makes 1
1 ripe mango
300ml milk of your choice (I prefer soy milk)
2 tsp ceremonial matcha powder (I like it strong but you can use less)
Around 30ml warm water
Dash of maple syrup (optional)
Ice cubes

Scoop the flesh of the mango out and add into a blender or processor (you can also mash with a fork). Blend for 30 seconds until pureed.

Prep your matcha whisk in hot water. Sift the matcha into a bowl, add the water and whisk in a zig zag motion until frothy.

Add the mango to a glass, then ice, maple syrup, milk and the matcha. Mix and enjoy!

title: Mango Matcha ü•≠
description:
My dream is to open an Asian caf√©, and I‚Äôm building a menu one drink at a time with you here! This Mango Matcha recipe is sweet, earthy, and absolutely perfect for summer. 

1 ripe mango 
2 tbsps honey 
1.5 tsps matcha powder 
2 Tbsps hot water 
1/2 cup milk of choice 
Lots of ice 

Process: 

- Chop the mango super fine, add honey and continue chopping 
- Pass the matcha powder through a sieve and whisk with a matcha bamboo whisk that has been soaked in water 
- Whisk until nice and frothy 
- To assemble, start with the mango at the base, Top up with ice, pour over the milk and the matcha 
- Stir and enjoy chilled!

#mangomatcha #mangobeverages #beverages #matcha #matchalovers

Matcha milk jellyüçµüíö you asked so here‚Äôs the recipe! #matcha #jelly #dessertideas #easyrecipe
description:
Matcha milk jellyüçµüíö

Recipe:
1. Bloom 1.25 tsp of gelatin powder in 1 tbsp of cold water
2. Whisk 2 tsp matcha powder with a little bit of hot water to make a paste
3. Heat 1 cup milk and add in 1 tbsp sugar 
4. Add gelatin to hot milk and mix until fully dissolved
5. Mix in matcha paste and pour into container
6. Let set for at least 4 hours
7. Cut into rectangular shapes and enjoy!

description:
This Dubai Chocolate Bar SNAPS!

‚ú®Recipe:
1 cup pistachio paste
1 to 1 ¬Ω cup shredded phyllo dough, cut into small pieces
vegetable oil
2 to 3 cups milk chocolate, melted
¬º cup white chocolate, melted
1 cup flour 
¬Ω cup corn starch
¬º tsp salt
2 tbsp oil
1 ¬Ω cup water

1. In a mold, drizzle white chocolate over and heat baking chocolate (not too hot so it looses it‚Äôs temper) as the first layer. Place in the fridge to let that layer set 

Making the Shredded Phyllo Dough (homemade because everywhere is sold out):
1. In a bowl add the flour, cornstarch, salt, oil & water together, whisk until completely smooth. 
2. Strain out all the lumps from the batter and fill a squeeze tube fitted with a super tiny nozzle.
3. Squeeze a small amount of batter out in thin strands until fried. Place aside when they start to pull up.

2. In a pan add the shredded phyllo dough with a small amount of frying oil. Fry until golden brown. Add the pistachio paste and mix together. 
3. Add another layer of melted tempered chocolate overtop of the mold. Set in the fridge until completely harden
4. Pop out of the mold, listen to that ASMR crack and enjoy üòâ

title: Is the VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE MILKSHAKE worth the hype?
description:
Is the VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE MILKSHAKE worth the hype?

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 2-3 cups vanilla ice cream
‚Ä¢ 1 ¬Ω cups knafeh (shredded phyllo dough)
‚Ä¢ 8 oz jar pistachio spread
‚Ä¢ 8 oz semi-sweet baking chocolate
‚Ä¢ Neutral oil, for frying

Directions:
1. Melt the baking chocolate over low heat until smooth. Pour the melted chocolate into a 16 oz flexible plastic cup and rotate to coat the inside.
2. Freeze the cup for 20‚Äì30 minutes, or until the chocolate is fully set.
3. In a blender, combine the vanilla ice cream, pistachio spread, and fried knafeh. Blend until smooth and creamy.
4. Pour the milkshake into your chocolate-coated cup and top with extra knafeh, pistachio drizzle, or whipped cream if you‚Äôre feeling fancy.
5. Serve immediately and enjoy this ultra-luxe, TikTok-worthy shake! üíö‚ú®

title: This VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE STRAWBERRY CUP is like a spoonful of MAGIC!
description:
This VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE STRAWBERRY CUP is like a spoonful of MAGIC!

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 (16 oz) cup
‚Ä¢ Strawberries, sliced
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp unsalted butter
‚Ä¢ Kataifi, shredded
‚Ä¢ Pistachio spread
‚Ä¢ Semi-sweet bakers chocolate

Directions:
1. In a medium pan on medium heat, add the butter kataifi and stir until kataifi starts browning. Remove from heat and mix in the pistachio spread.
2. Melt the chocolate, adding a little to the bottom of your cup. Place some sliced strawberries around the edges of the cup, then start layering alternate layers of the pistachio mixture, strawberries, and chocolate.
3. Top with a few more strawberries, serve immediately, and enjoy! üòä

title: Can these PISTACHIO BROWNIES beat out the Dubai chocolate bar? #summervibes
description:
Can these PISTACHIO BROWNIES beat out the Dubai chocolate bar? #summervibes

‚ú®recipe: 
16 oz Chocolate
1 ¬Ω cup (3 sticks) Unsalted Butter
2 ¬Ω cup Sugar
2 ¬Ω cup Flour
¬Ω cup Cocoa Powder
2 tsp Salt
4 Eggs
4 tsp Vanilla Extract

Directions:
1. Chop chocolate into bite sized pieces. In a saucepan on medium heat, melt butter and add in chocolate. Stir until completely melted and combined.
2. In a separate bowl, mix sugar, cocoa powder, and salt. Once mixed, add eggs, and vanilla. Whisk until combined and rolling off whisk in ribbons.
3. Sift in flour and using a spatula, fold into batter. Add in melted chocolate/butter and fold until smooth. Add remaining chocolate chunks.
4. Place batter into a greased 9x13 glass pan lined with parchment paper. Dollop pistachio butter and swirl into batter using a knife. Top with finely chopped pistachio nuts and bake at 325¬∞F for 45 minutes.
5. Let cool slightly outside of oven until you can handle the pan with your bare hands. Place into fridge and let cool for 1 hour.
6. Cut into 1 ¬Ω inch squares, serve and enjoy! üòâ

Hola Curiosones ‚ù§Ô∏è Aqu√≠ os dejo la receta casera pensada para una tableta de chocolate normal:

Ingredientes!

Para el chocolate:

200 gramos de chocolate blanco o con leche de buena calidad.
Colorante alimentario en gel (opcional), en colores como rosa, azul o amarillo.
Para el relleno:

150 gramos de crema de pistacho (puedes comprarla o prepararla en casa).
100 gramos de fideos de semolina (tipo cabello de √°ngel) o masa kataifi.
2 cucharadas de aceite de oliva.
Instrucciones:

Preparar el relleno:

Tostar los fideos de semolina o masa kataifi: Calienta el aceite de oliva en una sart√©n a fuego medio. A√±ade los fideos o la masa y tu√©stalos hasta que est√©n dorados y crujientes. Este paso es esencial para lograr la textura crujiente caracter√≠stica del chocolate de Dub√°i.
Mezclar con la crema de pistacho: Una vez que los fideos est√©n listos, mezcla con la crema de pistacho hasta obtener una masa homog√©nea. Reserva.
Preparar el chocolate:

Derretir el chocolate: Trocea el chocolate y derr√≠telo al ba√±o mar√≠a o en el microondas en intervalos de 30 segundos, removiendo entre cada uno, hasta que est√© completamente derretido y suave.
Colorear el chocolate (opcional): Si deseas a√±adir l√≠neas de colores al exterior, divide el chocolate derretido en porciones y a√±ade unas gotas de colorante alimentario a cada una. Mezcla bien hasta obtener los colores deseados.
Montar la barra de chocolate:

Formar la base: Vierte una capa de chocolate derretido en un molde para barras de chocolate, cubriendo el fondo. Deja que se enfr√≠e ligeramente.
A√±adir el relleno: Coloca la mezcla de crema de pistacho y fideos sobre la capa de chocolate, distribuy√©ndola uniformemente.
Cubrir con m√°s chocolate: Vierte otra capa de chocolate derretido sobre el relleno, asegur√°ndote de cubrirlo completamente.
A√±adir las l√≠neas de colores: Si has preparado chocolate de diferentes colores, utiliza una cuchara o una manga pastelera para a√±adir l√≠neas decorativas sobre la capa superior de chocolate. Puedes crear patrones seg√∫n tu preferencia.
Enfriar y desmoldar:

Deja que la barra de chocolate se enfr√≠e a temperatura ambiente y luego refrig√©rala durante al menos 2 horas, o hasta que est√© completamente s√≥lida.
Una vez firme, desm√≥ldala con cuidado.
Consejos adicionales:

Crema de pistacho casera: Si prefieres hacerla en casa, tritura pistachos pelados con az√∫car y un poco de aceite hasta obtener una pasta suave.
Variaciones: Puedes experimentar con diferentes tipos de chocolate (negro, con leche, blanco) y a√±adir otros ingredientes como frutos secos o frutas deshidratadas al relleno.

Disclaimer: I‚Äôm not a diabetic. Results are different for each person, especially for diabetics & can change from recipe to recipe. My own results vary a little day to day. Ideally, each person should tests on themselves. Glycemic load, calories, quality & quantity of food, all of these matter. Finally, I am not a doctor & this is not medical advice. 
.
How to see my results: Best is to get an idea of which foods spike more and which ones spike less, and develop an intuition based on ingredients. Don‚Äôt focus on absolute numbers. 
.
Why I‚Äôm doing this if I‚Äôm not a diabetic: I‚Äôve noticed that having steady glucose levels makes me feel good & I get lesser food cravings. Plus, prevention is the best medicine. Research today shows that high blood sugar variability over time can lead to diabetes, heart disease & obesity. Please see the work of Dr. Rob Lustig, Dr. Casey Means, Dr. Michael Snyder & Jessie Inchausp√©.
.

1. Blood sugar increase after eating = 30-40mg/dl or lower
